This is a personal mechanical engineering portfolio designed as a switchable OS-themed desktop.

Rules — enforce strictly on every file:
- No gradients except inside Windows95.tsx and WindowsXP.tsx title bars (period-accurate only)
- No border-radius except where OS theme explicitly requires it (macOS only)
- No glassmorphism, no box shadows except OS-accurate ones
- No generic card grids, no hero sections, no startup aesthetics
- Default font everywhere: IBM Plex Mono
- Three OS themes: Windows95, WindowsXP, Windows10
- OS theme is global state in lib/osContext.tsx, switchable at any time
- All windows are draggable via framer-motion
- Window chrome (title bar, borders, buttons) comes from the active OS theme
- Content components (AboutWindow, ProjectsWindow etc.) are OS-agnostic
- Content components receive styling tokens from the active OS theme, never hardcode colors
- OSPicker.tsx is the entry point — minimal, near-black background, three OS choices, small note saying "you can change this later"
- SettingsPanel.tsx is accessible from within any OS desktop to switch themes
- Desktop icons represent files: about, projects, experience, education, resume, contact
- Clicking a desktop icon opens a draggable window with that content
- File naming convention follows the active OS (e.g. about.exe on Windows, About.app on macOS)
- Never hardcode colors or fonts inside content window components — always receive from OS theme
